71.5	Peter_Falk	Peter Falk	Peter Michael Falk (September 16, 1927 â€“ June 23, 2011) was an American actor, best known for his role as Lieutenant Columbo in the television series Columbo. He appeared in numerous films such as The Princess Bride, The Great Race and Next, and television guest roles and was nominated for an Academy Award twice (for 1960's Murder, Inc. and 1961's Pocketful of Miracles), and won the Emmy Award on five occasions (four for Columbo) and the Golden Globe award once. Director William Friedkin, when discussing Falk's role in his 1978 film The Brink's Job said that "Peter has a great range from comedy to drama. He could break your heart or he could make you laugh."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/86/Peter_Falk_Columbo.JPG/220px-Peter_Falk_Columbo.JPG
